21/12/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Albania and Greece have signed an agreement on co-operation in coastal border control, the Albanian Ministry of Public Order announced on Tuesday (20 December). 
The document was sealed in Tirana on Monday.
In other news, Albanian Prime Minister Sali Berisha traveled to Iraq on Tuesday. 
He is meeting with members of the Albanian contingent deployed in Mosul as part of the international coalition. 
(Albanian News - 21/12/05)
